version_description: I have modified the chords in the verses to make them incorporate some harmony notes in vocals. (Much like the Dmaj7 chord in ’This Boy’)The previously submitted versions did not include the E/B chord in the line “For red is the colour that my baby wore ( As well as in the subsequent verses)as well as the G# chord over the first ’true’ in the closing sequence “Yes it is it’s true, yes it is it’s true ) The G# is included in version #1 but this version does not indicate it’s appearance as closing out the song -as another bridge follows it on that version.-I have also tabbed out the short guitar passage that closes the track after the vocals--not included in any previously-submitted version.
Simpler way to achieve right key, played in D with a capo. Full chord legend included.
